":{"id":"qA-b1CdeofKc"},"source":["#### Activity 2: Area of Triangle\n","\n","Create a function `tri_area()` that accepts `base` and `height` of a triangle as input parameters and returns its area.\n","\n","**Example**\n","```\n","1. tri_area(3, 2) ➞ 3\n","\n","2. tri_area(7, 4) ➞ 14\n","\n","3. tri_area(10, 10) ➞ 50\n","```\n","\n","**Note:**\n","\n","Area of a triangle is : $$\\frac{(base * height)} {2}$$\n","\n","\n","\n","Follow the steps given below to achieve the desired result:\n","\n","  - **Step 1**: Define a function `tri_area()` with base and height as parameters.\n","\n","  - **Step 2**: Calculate the area of triangle by using its formula and store the result in the variable `area`.\n","\n","  - **Step 3**: Return the calculated result using `return` statement.\n","\n","  - **Step 4**: Call the `tri_area()` function.\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"AtvPTG3kpBoS","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1623074313082,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":12,"user":{"displayName":"Isabella Schoffler","photoUrl":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhLOIF36CttK97G8Q1cIOIFUaFGwg0Je1g5W1YY=s64","userId":"16198738062751160932"}},"outputId":"e187deb1-9e12-4c4b-a305-95b6e3d57eb2"},"source":["# Write your code here\n","# Step 1: Define a function 'tri_area()'\n","def tri_area(base,height):\n","  area=(base*height)/2\n","\t# Step 2: Calculate area using the formula\n","  return area\n","\t# Step 3: Return the calculated area\n","\t\n","# Step 4: Call the 'tri_area()' function \n","\n","tri_area(10,9)"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["45.0"]},"metadata":{"tags":[]},"execution_count":1}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"KOVBiUSMzut1"},"source":["---"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"b4aeCDi0pkJz"},"source":["#### Activity 3: Appending lists\n","\n","Create two different lists which consist of any random numbers and append the second list 